<p>Step by Step instructions to install Oracle Applications R12(12.1.1) on Oracle Enterprise Linux 4 or RHEL 4 are described in this article. This is a single node installation, meaning that the database, all product directories and AD core directories, and all servers (concurrent processing, forms, and Web) are installed on a single node under one common APPL_TOP. </p> <p>Rapid Install installs the Java Development Kit (JDK) 5.0 automatically. Oracle Applications Software from Oracle eDelivery is already staged. If you have got the CDs, Stage them using <I>$ perl /mnt/cdrom/Disk1/rapidwiz/adautostg.pl</I></p> <div style="text-align: center; clear: both"><img title="Oracle Applications R12 Installation on Linux 029" alt="Oracle Applications R12 Installation on Linux 029" src="http://4.bp.blogspot.com/-gL9_V9ATkaE/TtUeRTkRePI/AAAAAAAAAv8/GZXCmDXYjJE/s1600/Oracle+Applications+R12+Installation+029.gif">     <br></div> <p>Here is the environment I have used in the installation process:</p> <div style="text-align: center; clear: both">  <table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="2" width="573" align="center"><tbody>      <tr>        <td valign="top" width="153" align="left"><font color="#0000ff">OS</font></td>         <td valign="top" width="418" align="left"><font color="#0000ff">OEL 4 Update 8</font></td>      </tr>       <tr>        <td valign="top" width="153" align="left"><font color="#0000ff">Memory</font></td>         <td valign="top" width="418" align="left"><font color="#0000ff">12GB</font></td>      </tr>       <tr>        <td valign="top" width="153" align="left"><font color="#0000ff">Disk Space</font></td>         <td valign="top" width="418" align="left"><font color="#0000ff">100GB Disk (73GB required for fresh install ; 161GB for Vision)</font></td>      </tr>       <tr>        <td valign="top" width="153" align="left"><font color="#0000ff">Server Name</font></td>         <td valign="top" width="418" align="left"><font color="#0000ff">erp.freeoraclehelp